# Repository Safety

- Never work directly on main.
- Never push directly to main.
- Never edit, expose, print, or commit environment files or secrets.
- Never delete or rewrite working features without explicit approval.
- Never modify files unrelated to the approved task.
- Never perform a broad refactor unless explicitly approved.
- Preserve existing routes and working user flows.
- Preserve Supabase UUID patients and numeric demo patients.
- Keep measured clinical values separate from AI interpretation.
- Do not add dependencies without explaining the need first.
- Before editing, list the expected files and the smallest safe plan.
- After editing, run relevant tests and the production build.
- Report changed files, test results, and remaining risks.
- Never commit, push, or merge unless explicitly instructed.
